title: (x) Chanel Paris, Kim & Kokino thin stressed sans - Retro Super Skinny, Stilla {Ignacio, Conor}
author: coupdegrace

comments.content:
The ampersand is [Stilla](http://web.archive.org/web/20120504100103/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/ef/stilla/).

What you’re looking for reminded me of this thread:  
 [http://www.typophile.com/node/20952](http://web.archive.org/web/20120504100103/http:/www.typophile.com/node/20952)

It’s certainly has an air of Peignot about it.

The other one is Stark Semi-Bold, Phil's Homage To The Alphabet, page 345.  
Probably not available for purchase, at least with that name becouse this is not the [one](http://web.archive.org/web/20120504100103/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/urw/stark/).
You never know, I just ran into Mike Rossi's [Retro Super Skinny](http://web.archive.org/web/20120504100103/http:/www.subflux.com/Fonts/FontsRecre_Idle.htm).
